opposition candidate cuauhtemoc cardenas 
claimed victory in mexicos presidential elections saturday a day 
before the government planned to release the official results 
we have won the presidential elections the national 
democratic front candidate said we will not recognize 
authorities that might rise out of electoral fraud 
there was no immediate response from the governing institutional 
revolutionary party or its candidate carlos salinas de gortari 
which have also claimed victory 
cardenas told reporters he had won 10 of 31 states and the 
federal district which includes mexico city 
he said his victory claim was based on projections drawn from 
results leaked by the government and his leftofcenter coalitions 
own count of 67 million votes mexico has more than 38 million 
registered voters 
cardenas said he would win with 388 percent of the vote 
he said salinas would have 3269 percent winning five states 
and conservative national action party candidate manuel clouthier 
would be third with 255 percent of the vote winning in five 
states 
the federal election commission said saturday it would give the 
final official results from the presidential and congressional 
races to the political parties on sunday 
while cardenas and the governing party both claimed victory 
clouthier said saturday he was ahead in the national vote count he 
also announced a series of nationwide protests against fraud 
i summon you to declare yourselves in civil resistance from 
this moment on clouthier said told tens of thousands of 
supporters in mexico citys huge main plaza 
in northern mexico hundreds of national action party backers 
occupied one of four international bridges linking ciudad juarez 
with el paso texas saturday night in a driving rainstorm they 
vowed to remain until official election results were announced 
the party claimed it had taken four districts in juarez from 
institutional revolutionary party 
clouthier said institutional revolutionary party was now the 
third political force in the country 
his campaign manager francisco gonzalez garza said the 
national action party tally showed clouthier winning at least four 
senate seats and 12 of mexico citys 40 voting districts 
the institutional revolutionary party also released results 
saturday from what it said was 67 million votes 
the governing party said the results showed salinas leading with 
4869 percent of the vote cardenas second with 2716 percent and 
clouthier third with 1895 percent 
cardenas had earlier claimed winning the capital home to a 
fourth of mexicos 80 million people and institutional 
revolutionary party officials said privately they might have to 
concede the capital and the states of michoacan morelos and mexico 
to him 
the institutional revolutionary party has not lost a 
presidential gubernatorial or senate race since it was founded in 
1929 
like clouthier cardenas accused the governing party of 
widespread fraud in the elections 
cardenas earlier accused the governing party of trying to steal 
his mexico city triumph by demanding a recount in the federal 
district or seeking to nullify his votes 
i call upon the president of the republic and candidate carlos 
salinas de gortari to comply with their word and their commitment 
to preserve the legality of this electoral process he said 
the institutional revolutionary party has ordered local election 
officials in the capital to file formal complaints about what it 
claims are multiple votes for cardenas the government newspaper el 
nacional said saturday 
cardenas is on the ballot as the candidate of three parties 
after these parties officially unified behind him the 
institutional revolutionary partydominated election commission 
rejected a cardenas request to list him only once 
the institutional revolutionary party is claiming thousands of 
voters marked several party symbols on their ballot to vote for 
cardenas and that each mark was counted as a separate vote 
the opposition and citizen watchdog groups have been accusing 
the governing party of vote fraud since the polls closed on 
wednesday 
the assembly for effective suffrage a watchdog group said it 
found 1100 irregularities ranging from ballotstuffing and 
tampering with voter rolls 
alfonso bravo of the citizens assembly reported 
irregularities in 20 percent of the nearly 28000 voting booths it 
had monitored 
