rain was scattered across sections of the plains and upper great 
lakes on sunday but not enough to cancel the drought and one 
kentucky utility said stricter water conservation may be needed 
kentucky gov wallace wilkinson has called a special water 
emergency meeting for monday to discuss with local government 
